cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with hyperspectral image super-resolution using unsupervised learning and mutual information. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of mutual information and the collaborative $l_{2,1}$ norm suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
